Name: NLP
Author: Matteo Capelletti
Date: 21/05/05
email: Matteo.Capelletti@let.uu.nl
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
General description:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
NLP is a parser for the Non-associative Lambek calculus with product (NL).
It implements the basic methods for parsing with Lambek grammars developed 
in my PhD thesis: Parsing with Structure-Preserving Categorial Grammars, 
Utrecht University, 2007. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Description of the modules:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Main.hs: high level functions. To start parser call the function main. 
         This gives you a series of options.
         
Data.hs: all the data types, basic utilities, show and latex functions.

ER.hs: reduces the computation of an NL grammar to the computation of the equivalent Ajdukiewicz-Bar Hillel grammar.

Mix.hs: the recognizer.

Parse.hs: the parser.

Lexer.hs: parser combinators for reading the fragments.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Unzip the folder in some location.
The folder Lex contains some sample fragments. You can extend them or create 
new ones, with extension .nlp. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage: 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) $ ghci Main.hs
2) Main> main

The current version contains a couple of commands specific to Mac. 
If you don't have a Mac, just change the function tex in Main.hs